@saimn This can be solved by initializing ``aperture_radius`` with a positive float value when creating a ``IterativelySubtractedPSFPhotometry`` object.

> Is it required to use a photutils-specific PSF object ?

In principle, no. ``psf_model`` should be any ``astropy.modeling.Fittable2DModel`` which meets the criterion of having ``x_0``, ``y_0``, and ``flux`` as parameters.

