@abalkin I was cleaning up in the `tzfile` implementation anyway when trying to get a handle on #112, so I implemented the above solution. The behavior is now consistent with `pytz`'s behavior, at least (as far as I can tell), though we're subject to the same bug in the Portugal zone in 1940.

I don't think there's much to be done about it, though. A heuristic that covers that use case would be to check if the dst() values calculated based on the STD->DST transition is different from the DST->STD transition, and if it is, check it against the next zone transition boundary, and if that one matches one of the two transitions, fill in the uncertain one with the more popular value.

In the end, it would be nice to get the SAVE values directly from tzdata, but I think generally people will prefer to use the compiled binaries stored in the OS, so it's quite a lot of work for such a rare edge case.

